oun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 6594, \"to\": 6606}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But China soon hit back at the anger, with the Xinhua news agency branding the backlash 'hypocritical' and 'irresponsible'.\", \"from\": 6609, \"to\": 6732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6613, \"end\": 6618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999977335392, \"rank\": 1.7344753019988883e-09, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 6656, \"end\": 6662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.309832849834382e-46, \"text\": \"Xinhua\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 6663, \"end\": 6667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_media\", \"score\": 0.9616535795220741, \"rank\": 0.039875486964512284, \"text\": \"news\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_media\"}, {\"begin\": 6668, \"end\": 6674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertising_agency\", \"score\": 0.9999993761632268, \"rank\": 6.170231068635067e-07, \"text\": \"agency\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertising_agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertising_agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the anger\", \"from\": 6636, \"to\": 6645}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The group singled out the-then Senate majority leader, Harry Reid, who had called for the uniforms to be piled up and 'burned'.\", \"from\": 6733, \"to\": 6860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6764, \"end\": 6770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Senate\", \"score\": 0.9999982672731226, \"rank\": 1.732728946166949e-06, \"text\": \"Senate\", \"ty